Hello STS developers

I have read:

* [request mappings view doesn't respect @GetMapping, @PostMapping etc. #101](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-ide/issues/101)

Now I am working with:

```
Spring Tool Suite 

Version: 3.9.1.RELEASE
Build Id: 201710111105
Platform: Eclipse Oxygen.1a (4.7.1a)
```
Thus for a `Spring Framework` Web Application working with `Gradle` through _multi-modules_, for a module named `web-29-controller`, right click -> `Spring Tools` -> `Add Spring Project Nature`

For that module I have:

```
@Configuration
@RequestMappingsViewProfile
@ComponentScan(basePackages="com.manuel.jordan.controller")
public class RequestMappingsViewConfig {

	@Bean
	public String requestMappingsView(){
		throw new RuntimeException("This @Configuration with @Bean NEVER must be created in runtime");
	}

}
```

Where `@RequestMappingsViewProfile` applies to the `request-mappings-view` profile

Thus the following is mandatory:

* `web-29-controller`, right click -> `Properties` 

and then

